<br>
TUvyn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upaldor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Paldor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/7/01 10:29:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quading Cougars......</span><hr size=1> Cougars are animals...<br>
<br>
So you have two strategies for cougars that aggro on you when quad kiting.<br>
<br>
You can use FEAR ANIMAL and get rid of an extra cougar...Or you can ROOT an extra cougar.<br>
<br>
<br>
Either way, you do need to get away from the extra mob, so that it will not re-aggro on you when the spell breaks.<br>
<br>
-=-=-<br>
<br>
It sounds more like you need to practice your quad-kiting ability... I sugest you go to a newbie area like Steamfont or Butcherblock and practice quading low green mobs.  <br>
<br>
(Meaning practice gettting them together in a tight group, and never letting them hit you.. if you cast a nuke it will probably kill them in one shot,  You can use HARMONY as your pretend "nuke" spell and see that it effects all your kited mobs).<br>
<br>
Practice getting them together, and also practice avoiding other mobs as you kite (like if you see a large rat about to get near you, practice avoiding the rat while still keeping away from your kitied mobs).<br>
<br>
If you mess up you will never die and it will help your technique.<br>
<br>
Druids are able to quad kite in VERY small areas, it just takes practice and patience. <p><table width="75%" border="0">
