Guaranteed 100% E-Bay free.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udobbanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dobbanz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/8/01 8:58:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quading Cougars......</span><hr size=1> Another good idea when quadding cougars is to bring them to the shore area when you start to kite them this way you have a lot of running room and nothing spawns along the shores of the first island. Also to get practice id reccomend starting with kiting 2 at once then working your way up to 4 as your technique improves.<br>
<br>
