<br>
Head to the South coast of the main island in Iceclad.  That coast is pretty safe toward the EW bridge.  I usually pull 4 wolves down to that coast and run them up and down the coast.  No other mobs to get in the way and hardly ever any people.<br>
<br>
Rolfe of Povar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/userberus00.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Serberus00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/12/01 4:41:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quading Cougars......</span><hr size=1> The Dire Wolves in Iceclad are excellent experience, but the loot is non existant, I did the with one druid from 40 to 44, made about one level every day (approx 4-5 hours a day). This time round i'm doing the dire wolves in Great Divide, a drakkel dire wolf, primarily because they have +CoV +Coldain faction and they give reasonable experience.<br>
<br>
I'd rather be quadding the dires in IC to level faster, but i'm willing to level a little slower in order to have a great mix of exp, faction and loot (they drop belt things, forgotten the name)<br>
<br>
As for cougars, first druid I quadded on the gnome island, just try to stay along the shore, second druid I did the ToFS island, the tofs island is easier, there are LOADS of cougars round the back of ToFS and there is never really anyone on the second island.<br>
<br>
I seemed to get more cougar claw earrings too, it was boring selling all 15 of them =P (about 9-10 levels of hunting)<br>
<br>
Serberus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utuvynstormweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tuvyn Stormweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/19/01 5:36:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quading Cougars......</span><hr size=1> OK i got to quading things in ew... cus im now in 40... so thanks for tips<br>
